  "doc_id": "5112",
  "text": "Our compilation tools are based on constraint automata [CITATION_1] , introduced by Baier et al. as a semantics for Reo. Constraint automata are a general formalism for describing systems behavior. They have been used to model not only Reo connectors but also, for instance, actor-based systems [CITATION_2] . For Reo, a constraint automaton specifies when during execution of a connector which data items flow where. Whenever the particular data values communicated through a connector do not matter (i.e., whenever only synchronization matters), constraint automata can be simplified into port automata (pa) [CITATION_3] . Because data forms an orthogonal concern to the material presented in this paper, we focus our attention on port automata.",
